description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community RGN– Band 5 Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full AND part time hours available.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BASED AT LONG SUTTON/SPALDING&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS SUITABLE FOR STUDENTS NEWLY QUALIFYING TO APPLY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours are 7.5 hrs a day covering 8.00 – 19.00 7 days a week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have exciting new roles and opportunities in Lincolnshire Community Health Services NHS Trust (LCHS). Our staff collectively see thousands of people every day in community hospitals, health clinics, schools, children’s centres and in patients’ own homes. They also do something else very special; they are responsible for turning an ordinary day into something extraordinary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for brilliant individuals who can be part of a fast-moving, innovative and ambitious team, dedicated to supporting members of our communities to manage their own health at home and reduce the need to go into hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are rated ‘Outstanding’ by the Care Quality Commission and are playing an integral part in shaping future health service provision countywide alongside partner health and social care organisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not only will our successful candidates have the opportunity to flourish in a successful NHS Trust, Lincolnshire offers some of the best schools in the country, affordable housing and a great standard of living in one of the many picturesque market towns, villages or a thriving city.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lincolnshire Community Health Services NHS Trust is a vibrant and creative organisation which provides a diverse range of clinical services across Lincolnshire. We pride ourselves in putting ‘Patients First’ and are seeking enthusiastic individuals who shares these values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We pride ourselves on offering career development opportunities to all our staff. Through appraisal and regular feedback from your manager we will work with you to support your chosen career pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The community nursing teams in LCHS are supported by case managers and the successful candidates will be developed to follow a link nurse role in a clinical area which will aid the career progression of the staff member.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As this is a community post, you must be able to travel across the County to locations not served by public transport&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust actively encourages training and development in line with service need, they also supported exiting opportunities in IT with each staff member being supplied with a laptop for documenting onto the patient record in the patient’s own home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;These posts will be initially based with this team in Long Sutton/Spalding but will be reviewed at 6 &amp; 12 months, and there may be need to move bases across South Lincolnshire depending on service need.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tara Smith: 07824 820834&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Debbie Wilson: 07717540530&lt;/p&gt;
